        "description": "<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Naoe glares at an unidentified guy who\u2019s probably gonna betray her in Assassin\u2019s Creed Shadows canon mode\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Ubisoft Quebec/Ubisoft via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/ac-shadows-canon-mode.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><strong>Canon mode</strong> is a setting in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/assassins-creed-shadows/40930\">Assassin\u2019s Creed Shadows</a></em>. Like all the familiar boot-up settings \u2014 subtitle preferences, game difficulty, <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/542384\">immersive mode</a>, <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/540855\">guided exploration mode</a>, and so on \u2014 you\u2019ll choose whether or not to activate it before starting a new game. But the thing is, once you select it, you can\u2019t change it. You\u2019re locked in.</p>\n\n<p class=",
